1)Where do you all set up when pulling there. <br>
2) What level do the guards start turning light blue.  <br>
3) Any tricks to splitting the pulls as a warrior.  <br>
4)Are there any pulling guides out there for Neriak?<br>
  Any and all help would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
Asland Lionheart <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utaminy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taminy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/26/02 12:31:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1316.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Neriak exp?</span><hr size=1> I can only tell you this from my experience. There may be other possible ways.<br>
<br>
1. I set up in The Blind Fish, the bar in the underground building which has the bank (in Neriak Commons). I pulled the bank guard first (runners head out the building going past the bank), and then exited the building and started pulling other guards. I've also set up in Neriak 3rd Gate (and have seen other people there as well), but I didn't like it as much. Some of the guards there are SKs and HT.<br>
<br>
2. The guards in Neriak Commons and Neriak 3rd Gate are almost entirely level 40. They go light blue at level 55. There are a few exceptions to this rule - there is a guard in Neriak Commons who is about level 15. There is also a Dragoon, level 45+ (dark blue at level 60) in Neriak Commons as well. I found the experience there still decent at 55, but it was terrible at 56. Also, the guards in Neriak Foreign Quarter are considerably lower level for the most part (level 35ish I believe).<br>
<br>
3. Just learn how to pull. I'm not sure exactly when they level split, but you'll find out if you can split them or not. Watch out for wanderers while pulling, and I'd reccomend using arrows if you can. Guards are one of the tougher mobs to proximity split. <br>
<br>
4. I don't know of any guides. <p><p><map name="FPMap0">
